snippet.textDisplay: I have had two shots, and two boosters, I am lucky to live in a more rural county that has a very high level of vaccinations, about the best in Minnesota. I have stopped masking when I go into the gas station, grocery store ect. but, when the parking lot is full, and, it looks like the store is crowded, I do wear a mask. We have a tourist economy, with attractions that draw folks from all over the country, and, in summer our stores are full of tourists. I guess it all comes down to personal choice. I am 73, and, in reasonable health, if I do get covid, I will probably be okay.  We all have to do what we feel is right for each of us, if I lived in an area of high transmission, I might do things differently.

snippet.textDisplay: @Jackie371 Outdoors is pretty safe if you aren't in a crowd or surrounded by people shouting. It is indoors with circulated air and poor ventilation where the disease can really spread and sty in the air for hours. It is getting up to triple digits here already, so we don't get to enjoy much time outside. Outside, I go maskless unless it is crowded like a street market. I have the CA Notify app, so if someone else also has the app, it will notify all possible exposed people if I test positive. I got an alert, but fortunately I had been wearing my mask and tested for 2 weeks. I didn't get it. Problem is, so few people actually bother to get the app and even less can be bothered to wear a mask indoors.
